31
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,200
Excuse me. Are you…

32
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:31,836
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

33
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:45,725
What's that?

34
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:50,730
Those punks.

35
00:03:56,027 --> 00:03:57,070
Oh, no.

36
00:03:58,112 --> 00:04:00,073
This is not how I wanted it to start.

37
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:05,870
You annoying bastard.

38
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:09,707
You're just dying
for a good beating, aren't you?

39
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:11,709
That's enough!

40
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,048
What the hell does he want?

41
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:21,594
Three ganging up on one?
Hey, that's cheap.

42
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:24,222
If you're drunk, keep on walking.

43
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:28,726
You won't be able to hold a spoon if
your last good hand is in a cast, mister.

44
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:30,770
Mister?

45
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:33,731
What the heck are you saying?

46
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:35,525
Looks like this guy won't listen.

47
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:37,443
A beating might do.

48
00:04:59,048 --> 00:05:02,302
HORANG TAEKWONDO
CERTIFICATE OF COMMENDATION

49
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:08,057
You can't do this, sir.

50
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,018
Or is this because I'm young?

51
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:13,146
You do look young for your age.

52
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:17,650
Those boys were ganging up on the kid!

53
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,736
Keep your voice down.
You're in a police station.

54
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:20,987
- Have a good one.
- You too.

55
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:24,198
Officer! Wait!

56
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,283
Shut up!

57
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:30,663
Shut your mouth, okay?

58
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:34,334
I can't sleep because of you.

59
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,170
Not again.

60
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,881
This is nuts!

61
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:42,508
You're here too.

62
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:44,510
This is actually good.

63
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,180
You saw them beat up a boy, right?

64
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:48,765
I did.

65
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:53,978
Did you really fight
those three teenage boys alone?

66
00:05:57,815 --> 00:06:01,527
Fortunately, I practiced tae kwon do
since I was little.

67
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:06,240
Did you perhaps get those men in here too?

68
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,326
Is he crazy? He's talking to himself.

69
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,789
Yes, I got them all in here
because they broke the law.

70
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:14,791
You break the law, you get punished.

71
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:19,003
You don't know when to gloss over things.

72
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:22,090
You shouldn't gloss things over!

73
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:24,300
If you make compromises and cut corners,

74
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:27,720
the world would become a total mess
in an instant, mister.

75
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:31,933
You see, my goal is
to make a fair and beautiful world

76
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:34,894
where social order is maintained
by the law

77
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:39,148
and people respect each other.

78
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:43,069
That's why you wanted to be an attorney.

79
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:47,031
For that to happen, I shouldn't be easy
even on minor misconduct.

80
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,911
Anyway,

81
00:06:51,994 --> 00:06:53,955
why do you speak to me so formally?

82
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:55,498
I'm a whole lot younger than you.

83
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:58,543
You're Attorney Han's older sister.

84
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:00,628
What?

85
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,880
I mean…

86
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:08,511
Okay, I'll be more casual with you.

87
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,346
Of course.

88
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:15,309
Anyway, I didn't mean
to get you locked up in here too.

89
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:17,270
I'm sorry.

90
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:23,985
Later when the officer comes,
I'll talk him into releasing you.

91
00:07:24,068 --> 00:07:27,405
You don't have to wait.
You can get out of here if you want.

92
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:30,450
What? How?

93
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,618
I'm behind steel bars…

94
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:42,879
Five fish altogether in one fish tank

95
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:48,509
Hello?

96
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,053
Is this Mr. Shin I-rang's brother-in-law?

97
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,930
Yes, this is me. Who may you be?

98
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:55,308
I'm Lieutenant Cho Chi-yeong
from Seocho Police Station.

99
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,685
Police?

100
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:01,147
Have you settled down now?

101
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:04,775
No, I'm boiling with anger.

102
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,487
I'm so young! Why did I die?

103
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:09,780
I know how you feel.

104
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,699
You must be sad and frustrated.

105
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:14,911
What's worse is
that I can't remember a thing.

106
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,288
You don't?

107
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,041
- That's strange.
- What do you mean?

108
00:08:20,124 --> 00:08:23,794
Ghosts float in mid-air
until they regain their memory.

109
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:26,130
But you're already on the ground.

110
00:08:27,256 --> 00:08:31,010
Anyway, I can help you regain your memory.

111
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:32,094
How?

112
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:35,932
If I tell you your name
and date of birth--

113
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,017
Tell me quick.

114
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:39,936
Your memory will come back.

115
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,604
Make it come back right now!

116
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,564
Okay, all right.

117
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,234
First, take a deep breath.

118
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:53,616
- Come on, mister!
- All right.

119
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:56,452
You've got a temper just like your sister.

120
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,083
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

121
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,088
Han So-hyun.

122
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:17,723
You were born on July 7, 1994.

123
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:27,692
HAN SO-HYUN

124
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:29,235
Sister.

125
00:09:31,028 --> 00:09:32,363
HORANG TAEKWONDO

126
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,158
Hey! Get your hands off her!

127
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,372
It's going to be real fun.

128
00:09:41,455 --> 00:09:42,832
Na-hyun!

129
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,715
So-hyun!

130
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:06,355
Na-hyun…

131
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:14,196
I…

132
00:10:20,077 --> 00:10:21,662
I saved her.

133
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,627
I saved my sister, Na-hyun.

134
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,214
I see.

135
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,387
I'm dead, but I'm happy.

136
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:42,099
Mister.

137
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,769
My sister

138
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,272
must be well and happy, right?

139
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,528
Oh, my head…

140
00:10:58,949 --> 00:11:01,202
How much did I drink?

141
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:13,339
What is Attorney Shin's jacket doing here?

142
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,183
Hello?

143
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:26,477
Attorney Han,
please help my brother-in-law!

144
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:28,813
Excuse me?

145
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,067
What year is it now?

146
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,195
It's 2025.

147
00:11:38,447 --> 00:11:40,074
Then,

148
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:42,576
thirty one…

149
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:45,955
I wonder if she became a singer.

150
00:11:47,289 --> 00:11:50,501
Oh, my sister's dream was to be a singer.

151
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,920
She just loved singing.

152
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:55,881
She'd sing and play the guitar all day.

153
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:58,717
Look.

154
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:01,804
Your sister isn't a singer--

155
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:04,223
Mr. Shin,
your attorney is here to see you.

156
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:13,941
Attorney Han…

157
00:12:20,197 --> 00:12:21,198
Han Na-hyun?

158
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:26,579
Is it really you?

159
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:31,041
What the… You became an attorney?

160
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,294
But why?

161
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:39,341
Wow, it's amazing.

162
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:42,678
The tiny little girl

163
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:45,890
turned into this awesome career woman.

164
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,145
Is this how you actually are?

165
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:57,276
I want you to take this first.

166
00:12:58,444 --> 00:12:59,945
I'm not thirsty.

167
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,573
Don't be so cold to him.

168
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:05,201
I'm not asking you to drink it.

169
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:09,121
If I act strange in any way,

170
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:11,081
splash that water on me.

171
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:12,500
Why should I?

172
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:15,294
I'm not like you. I don't use violence.

173
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,213
Yes, I know.

174
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,590
Still, keep it with you.

175
00:13:20,132 --> 00:13:24,136
I'd appreciate it if you could splash
that on me, in case I act weird.

176
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,805
You're doing me a favor.

177
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:28,474
That's not violence, right?

178
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:37,107
How are the boys?

179
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,985
They'll take two, two,
and four weeks to heal.

180
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:42,571
Do you usually have bad drinking habits?

181
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,824
How could you use violence
against students?

182
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:48,994
Na-hyun, that's not his fault.

183
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,246
I have nothing to say.

184
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:51,580
You better not.

185
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:56,126
I wouldn't have taken on this case
if not for your brother-in-law.

186
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:01,674
And I'm partly at fault
for drinking with you.

187
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:04,301
Thank you for choosing to be my attorney.

188
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:09,974
But three boys were ganging up on one kid.

189
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:12,184
I heard differently.

190
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:15,312
The boys were just talking

191
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,856
when you attacked them out of the blue.

192
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,944
That's not true!

193
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:24,655
I swear there were three bullying one.

194
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:27,116
And they attacked me first.

195
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:31,579
Three boys were bullying one,

196
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,581
and they attacked me first.

197
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,791
The four victims testified the same.

198
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:40,129
If you keep denying it, it'll be taken
to both criminal and civil suits.

199
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:44,717
If you don't settle with the parents
of Sung Min-jae with a four-week injury,

200
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,594
you'll get a six-month sentence, minimum.

201
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:49,430
Then, you'll lose your law license.

202
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:53,517
Don't jump to conclusions so easily
without even looking into it.

203
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,479
Don't you believe me?

204
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,231
It's best to reach a settlement.

205
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:02,735
Settle with them no matter what.

206
00:15:02,818 --> 00:15:04,403
Hey, you don't know anything!

207
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,239
I'll try.

208
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:08,908
Of course, you should.

209
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:14,330
Fortunately, the arrest warrant
was dismissed.

210
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:15,748
Go back home for now.

211
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:18,959
What kind of attorney are you?

212
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:25,549
An attorney is supposed to listen
to their client and side with them.

213
00:15:27,384 --> 00:15:28,802
Are you getting worked up at me?

214
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:30,429
You shouldn't do this to your client!

215
00:15:30,512 --> 00:15:32,640
Are you really the Han Na-hyun I know?

216
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:34,808
The Han Na-hyun you know?

217
00:15:35,684 --> 00:15:38,437
What do you even know about me?
Watch what you say.

218
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,939
So much for a drunk who beats kids.

219
00:15:40,564 --> 00:15:42,983
Those punks deserved a beating!

220
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:45,319
That's pretty low,
coming from an attorney.

221
00:15:45,402 --> 00:15:48,113
What made you become this inflexible?
You're darn annoying!

222
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,374
Darn annoying?

223
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:25,359
Did you say something to your sister?

224
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:27,820
I said she was darn annoying.

225
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:29,571
What?

226
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:33,325
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

227
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:37,037
But why is she so mean?

228
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:40,541
I'd be mad at someone
who beat high schoolers too.

229
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:41,875
No.

230
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:45,212
She isn't one to get angry
without even listening.

231
00:16:45,295 --> 00:16:47,631
It's so weird
that she became an attorney too.

232
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:50,384
Why don't you go after her
if you're that curious?

233
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,386
What about you?

234
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,347
The arrest warrant is dismissed,
so I'll be released soon.

235
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,307
Go on now.

236
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:09,361
- Over this amazing blue sky
- Oh, there she goes again.

237
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:12,656
- Riding on the flying magic carpet
- Magic carpet

238
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,950
- In this amazing
- In this amazing

239
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:17,161
- Dad, focus on driving!
- Blue world

240
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:19,955
You don't even listen to music now?

241
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:23,333
DAD

242
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,173
DAD

243
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,555
What changed you so much?

244
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,227
Wow.

245
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,314
My neighborhood hasn't changed at all.

246
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:48,067
That's a relief.

247
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:08,128
Dad?

248
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:25,187
He's got so much more gray hair.

249
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:29,191
And wrinkles too.

250
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:39,243
OFF-DUTY

251
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:46,250
Still, it's so nice…

252
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:50,045
to see you, Dad.

253
00:19:06,478 --> 00:19:08,814
Honey, I'm home.

254
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:15,946
This cushion is still here.

255
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:18,448
But the sofa is new.

256
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,284
It's nice.

257
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:22,744
Something smells delicious.

258
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,705
Welcome home. You must be hungry.

259
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:26,707
- Go wash your hands.
- Okay.

260
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:40,387
Mom.

261
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:50,689
Mom…

262
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:06,997
Wow.

263
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,666
Your braised tofu looks so good, Mom.

264
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,795
That doenjang stew looks delicious too.

265
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:16,757
There you go,
drinking straight soju again.

266
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,967
I told you to eat as you drink.

267
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:21,303
- Okay, fine.
- Here.

268
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:25,224
Did you try calling Na-hyun?

269
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:28,644
Yes, but she just wants to dine out.

270
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:30,729
I see.

271
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:33,106
What?

272
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:35,651
Are you sad that you can't cook
for our daughter?

273
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:37,569
No, it's not that.

274
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:41,198
I'm wondering if we should move.

275
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,410
I think she's avoiding this house.

276
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:47,788
No way.

277
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,373
She's extremely busy.

278
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:52,584
We should be grateful
that she's even making time for us.

279
00:20:54,294 --> 00:20:55,837
- You think?
- Of course.

280
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:01,176
Don't overthink it.

281
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,886
And don't walk on eggshells around her.

282
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:05,472
Look who's talking.

283
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:06,848
Geez.

284
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,726
Oh, the news must be on. What time is it?

285
00:21:10,602 --> 00:21:11,728
Gosh.

286
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:14,606
Han Na-hyun doesn't like this house?

287
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,653
And you walk on eggshells around her?

288
00:21:21,863 --> 00:21:22,864
Why?

289
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,618
Just why?

290
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,205
- On your 6:00.
- I know. I can hear it.

291
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:31,290
He's moving.

292
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:33,709
- I got him.
- Come on. He's fast.

293
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:35,210
- He's one tap.
- Okay.

294
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:37,170
- He's going down.
- Get him.

295
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:39,131
- Four o'clock.
- Where is he?

296
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:43,093
- Hold on. I'll help you.
- Dang.

297
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:45,470
- Hello?
- Darn, I'm out of ammo.

298
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:47,889
Gather up now.

299
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:49,725
- Where are you?
- Wait. Geez.

300
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:51,393
It must be nice to skip school,

301
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:53,437
away from your homeroom teacher.

302
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:55,188
Who are you?

303
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:56,648
I'm Attorney Yang Do-kyung.

304
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:59,443
Attorney? Doesn't that make us the boss?

305
00:21:59,526 --> 00:22:01,111
Yeah, of course.

306
00:22:02,112 --> 00:22:03,989
Mr. Attorney, we're busy right now.

307
00:22:04,072 --> 00:22:05,115
Crazy bastard.

308
00:22:05,782 --> 00:22:06,908
Visit us another time.

309
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:13,915
On behalf of you busy boys,
your parents hired me themselves.

310
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:19,212
They're quite angry
that their precious sons got beaten

311
00:22:19,713 --> 00:22:22,883
without knowing what you've done
to Jun-ho for the past year.

312
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,224
What happened that day?

313
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:37,647
We already told the police everything.

314
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:42,152
We were just messing around
when that lunatic came and did this to us.

315
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:44,946
- You're lying.
- No, it's true.

316
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,531
Let me tell you something important.

317
00:22:47,657 --> 00:22:50,410
That bastard who beat you up
got an attorney.

318
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:53,622
When it comes to relentlessness,
she's number one in this field.

319
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:55,665
It'll take no time for her

320
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:58,335
to find out what you've done.

321
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:03,965
You must be Min-jae.

322
00:23:06,259 --> 00:23:08,386
Your father is
the Vice-minister of Health and Welfare.

323
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:11,848
Ji-hyeok, your mother is
a professor of law at Hanguk University.

324
00:23:13,308 --> 00:23:17,229
Your parents will be put
in a tight spot if the truth gets out.

325
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:18,563
They'll kill me.

326
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:23,652
Right.

327
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:27,155
So now, be honest with me
about everything.

328
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,991
Only then, I can protect you.

329
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:33,954
I honestly don't care
about school violence.

330
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:36,081
What I want to know

331
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:38,625
is that attorney who assaulted you.

332
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:42,921
Didn't you find anything weird
about that bastard?

333
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,575
FILES
PARKING

334
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:31,029
My mom knows about it too?

335
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:32,113
Oh…

336
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:35,992
Well, she heard me talk
about the settlement money with Sa-rang…

337
00:25:36,826 --> 00:25:38,078
Even my sister?

338
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:42,582
Things happened that way.

339
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,836
Mother said she'd find a way
to get the money.

340
00:25:47,462 --> 00:25:51,883
As soon as she heard
you could lose your law license,

341
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:54,094
she stormed out.

342
00:25:55,553 --> 00:25:57,555
Still, she was understanding
after finding out

343
00:25:57,639 --> 00:25:59,975
that you were possessed
by Attorney Han's sister.

344
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:05,397
Your sister and I are trying every way
to get the money too, so don't worry.

345
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,193
- Bong-su.
- Yes?

346
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:13,071
I'm sorry.

347
00:26:13,697 --> 00:26:14,698
And thanks.

348
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:44,019
I'm sorry.

349
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:48,315
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

350
00:26:49,232 --> 00:26:51,860
You're in trouble because of me.

351
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:55,572
And I've discovered
the uncomfortable truth.

352
00:26:56,614 --> 00:26:58,742
What do you mean?

353
00:27:00,869 --> 00:27:04,414
Something's off
between Na-hyun and my parents.

354
00:27:05,749 --> 00:27:08,460
My family wasn't rich,

355
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,837
but we'd laugh and have fun.

356
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,630
We had the most positive energy.

357
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:16,634
Now, my parents
walk on eggshells around Na-hyun.

358
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:19,220
Na-hyun is really off too.

359
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:24,100
I wonder what happened.

360
00:27:24,684 --> 00:27:26,186
Something huge happened.

361
00:27:27,937 --> 00:27:31,358
They lost you, their precious family.

362
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:34,319
They must've been devastated.

363
00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:36,946
Oh.

364
00:27:38,948 --> 00:27:42,577
Why would a family drift apart
during sad times?

365
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:44,788
I wouldn't say they drifted apart.

366
00:27:46,456 --> 00:27:48,291
They're probably being considerate.

367
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:50,085
Considerate?

368
00:27:52,212 --> 00:27:53,922
Some kinds of sadness

369
00:27:54,672 --> 00:27:58,802
are so powerful that they quickly spread
to people around you.

370
00:28:06,059 --> 00:28:09,062
STORY WHERE HAPPINESS GROWS

371
00:28:14,943 --> 00:28:17,237
Worried that your sadness would spread,

372
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:19,864
you keep hiding your feelings,

373
00:28:20,573 --> 00:28:22,867
watch how you speak or behave,

374
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:25,078
and even

375
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:27,789
make secrets.

376
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:33,169
Because you try not to hurt
those around you,

377
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:36,464
you'd rather drift apart
from them little by little.

378
00:28:38,842 --> 00:28:42,679
I don't want my family
to live like this because of me.

379
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:47,308
It's so sad.

380
00:28:50,687 --> 00:28:55,400
All the ghosts who visited me
had their sad stories.

381
00:28:56,067 --> 00:28:57,527
But they all worked out.

382
00:28:58,611 --> 00:29:00,530
Now that you've come,

383
00:29:00,613 --> 00:29:03,032
your family may be able
to open up to each other.

384
00:29:03,867 --> 00:29:06,870
I'll do my best to help you.

385
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:10,165
Thank you.

386
00:29:13,543 --> 00:29:15,754
But your situation is more urgent.

387
00:29:16,504 --> 00:29:17,505
My situation?

388
00:29:18,089 --> 00:29:20,884
If your family loses your house
and business because of me,

389
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:22,051
it'll kill me.

390
00:29:22,135 --> 00:29:23,511
Wait.

391
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:25,096
Though I'm already dead.

392
00:29:26,347 --> 00:29:27,348
Anyway.

393
00:29:29,809 --> 00:29:30,810
You're

394
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:32,937
quite sweet.

395
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:35,523
I can't let go of anything
that feels wrong.

396
00:29:36,649 --> 00:29:39,152
What should we do to clear your name?

397
00:29:40,904 --> 00:29:43,406
If what you saw that day is true,

398
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:47,827
there has to be a reason why Jun-ho acts
like he isn't a victim of school bullying.

399
00:29:48,411 --> 00:29:51,080
That… is what you need to find out.

400
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:53,416
- What? Me?
- Yes.

401
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:55,210
How?

402
00:29:56,669 --> 00:29:58,338
You're a ghost, you know.

403
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:20,276
- Hello.
- Hello.

404
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:22,946
Hello.

405
00:30:38,753 --> 00:30:41,047
I'm sorry, but I don't know.

406
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:02,026
SUNG MIN-JAE

407
00:31:12,078 --> 00:31:14,330
- Hello--
- What took you so long to pick up?

408
00:31:16,457 --> 00:31:17,458
Sorry.

409
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:19,002
Who did you meet today?

410
00:31:19,586 --> 00:31:20,837
I didn't meet anyone.

411
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,922
If you get caught lying,
I'll kill you for real.

412
00:31:24,507 --> 00:31:25,758
I'm not lying.

413
00:31:29,512 --> 00:31:31,764
Come to Heaven and Earth
by 5:00 p.m. later today.

414
00:31:31,848 --> 00:31:33,099
Don't forget the money.

415
00:31:34,017 --> 00:31:35,226
Okay.

416
00:31:50,158 --> 00:31:52,368
Why are you doing this to me?

417
00:31:54,412 --> 00:31:55,496
What did I do…

418
00:31:56,497 --> 00:31:58,082
to deserve this?

419
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:09,093
I'm going to kill them.

420
00:32:20,605 --> 00:32:21,731
Who is it?

421
00:32:25,902 --> 00:32:27,862
Hello, I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

422
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:29,322
Attorney?

423
00:32:29,989 --> 00:32:31,699
Are you Jun-ho's mother?

424
00:32:32,825 --> 00:32:33,826
Yes.

425
00:32:34,577 --> 00:32:36,955
Did something happen with my son?

426
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:39,749
Didn't he tell you anything?

427
00:32:40,833 --> 00:32:44,170
I don't get to see him often
because I work at night.

428
00:32:45,171 --> 00:32:46,881
Did he cause some kind of trouble?

429
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:47,966
No.

430
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:51,970
Your son is involved in a small case,
but he's not an assailant.

431
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:57,642
Do you perhaps know where he may be?

432
00:33:05,108 --> 00:33:06,109
Jun-ho.

433
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:23,251
I saw it that day.

434
00:33:24,127 --> 00:33:25,461
Those guys were bullying you.

435
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:28,673
No, they're all my friends.

436
00:33:29,716 --> 00:33:31,926
- We were just messing around.
- They aren't…

437
00:33:33,052 --> 00:33:34,178
your friends.

438
00:33:34,846 --> 00:33:37,265
- You know that.
- I don't get what you're saying.

439
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:38,850
- Jun-ho.
- I'm leaving.

440
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:40,476
Hey, Seo Jun-ho!

441
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,025
So what are you going to do?

442
00:33:47,817 --> 00:33:48,860
What?

443
00:33:48,943 --> 00:33:51,029
What's your plan?
Are you really going to kill them?

444
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,408
Long ago,

445
00:33:56,409 --> 00:33:58,327
there was a guy like you
back in my school.

446
00:33:59,787 --> 00:34:01,956
He was harassed by school bullies,

447
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:05,209
but his parents and teachers
were clueless,

448
00:34:05,293 --> 00:34:07,587
not to mention his classmates.

449
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:08,880
So what?

450
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:10,715
Why are you telling me this?

451
00:34:10,798 --> 00:34:13,217
Guess why those guys hang out in packs.

452
00:34:13,968 --> 00:34:15,178
Because they're cowards.

453
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:17,930
So don't hide.

454
00:34:18,014 --> 00:34:20,308
Fight back when they come at you.

455
00:34:20,391 --> 00:34:22,393
No, I can't do that.

456
00:34:22,477 --> 00:34:25,354
Nothing is impossible.
Only if you make up your--

457
00:34:25,438 --> 00:34:26,981
I can't do it, okay?

458
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:29,525
I can't!

459
00:34:36,949 --> 00:34:39,202
Don't tell me…

460
00:34:40,787 --> 00:34:42,789
Do they have something on you?

461
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:46,918
I'm leaving.

462
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:48,961
Is that it?

463
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:50,630
What if I do?

464
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:53,758
Does it give me the right to kill them?

465
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:58,262
- Hello, Jun-ho.
- Jun-ho, hi!

466
00:34:58,346 --> 00:35:01,224
I'm going to take a super fun video
from now on.

467
00:35:01,307 --> 00:35:03,726
- Let go of me.
- Lights, ready?

468
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:06,437
- Hey, lights.
- One moment.

469
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:08,106
All ready now.

470
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:10,399
This bastard looks awfully pretty today.

471
00:35:10,483 --> 00:35:13,444
- Stop.
- Stay still for a sec, Jun-ho.

472
00:35:14,028 --> 00:35:15,655
They blackmailed you with it.

473
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:18,116
Yes.

474
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:22,370
Those scumbags took a video of me naked.

475
00:35:36,717 --> 00:35:39,637
Still, you shouldn't do the same to them.

476
00:35:40,847 --> 00:35:42,849
The guy I mentioned earlier

477
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:44,934
ended up in juvenile hall

478
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:48,020
after hitting those bullies with a brick.

479
00:35:49,021 --> 00:35:53,276
No one was there to understand
why he had to attack them.

480
00:35:54,277 --> 00:35:55,778
Your case will be the same.

481
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:58,698
You'll only suffer more.

482
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:01,409
So please.

483
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:04,620
Give me the knife.

484
00:36:05,746 --> 00:36:06,747
Now.

485
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:22,722
No, don't go!

486
00:36:22,805 --> 00:36:24,432
Don't go to them!

487
00:36:34,692 --> 00:36:37,069
An assailant can't meet a victim.
You know that.

488
00:36:38,404 --> 00:36:41,449
You should've told me
about the situation sooner.

489
00:36:42,158 --> 00:36:43,201
Unbelievable.

490
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:44,911
Sorry.

491
00:36:44,994 --> 00:36:47,371
Did Jun-ho tell you
where he's meeting up with the boys?

492
00:36:48,497 --> 00:36:50,958
Five o'clock at Heaven and Earth.

493
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:53,127
That means we have enough time.

494
00:36:54,045 --> 00:36:55,504
Heaven and Earth, right?

495
00:37:01,761 --> 00:37:02,970
Come on, follow me.

496
00:37:07,016 --> 00:37:08,768
POLICE STATION

497
00:37:08,851 --> 00:37:11,646
But this is only
Jun-ho's side of the story.

498
00:37:12,688 --> 00:37:14,023
You're right,

499
00:37:14,607 --> 00:37:18,861
but his classmates and the owner
of his part-time workplace

500
00:37:18,945 --> 00:37:22,490
saw a suspicious sight of school violence.

501
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:25,284
They also said they'd testify if needed.

502
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:27,328
I'd really appreciate your help.

503
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:36,420
Were they unable to help?

504
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:39,048
It seems like someone has to die
before they take action.

505
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:42,927
But we're running out of time.

506
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:46,097
I better take Jun-ho's video away
from them myself.

507
00:37:47,181 --> 00:37:51,352
It's the only evidence to prove
that they've been bullying him,

508
00:37:51,435 --> 00:37:54,021
let alone the day of the case.

509
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:56,482
Sounds good. Let's go right away.

510
00:37:56,565 --> 00:37:58,943
No, not with you.

511
00:37:59,026 --> 00:38:02,822
They know what you look like.
What if they recognize you and run off?

512
00:38:03,406 --> 00:38:06,158
But I can't let you go alone.

513
00:38:06,742 --> 00:38:08,661
I know you better than that.

514
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:10,830
There's another reason, isn't there?

515
00:38:11,414 --> 00:38:12,748
Yes.

516
00:38:12,832 --> 00:38:15,751
He can get another knife anytime.

517
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:18,796
Now that I know, I must stop him.

518
00:38:23,092 --> 00:38:25,803
He's a diligent kid that will be happy

519
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:28,597
if he can just get over this hump.

520
00:38:28,681 --> 00:38:30,683
A boy's life is on the line here.

521
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:32,810
I'm going to do something about it.

522
00:38:33,894 --> 00:38:35,896
Don't ever come
inside the Internet café, okay?

523
00:38:36,605 --> 00:38:37,606
Okay.

524
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:41,110
I'll wait nearby and only stop Jun-ho.

525
00:38:41,193 --> 00:38:43,946
Instead, my brother-in-law
will be there to assist you.

526
00:39:38,584 --> 00:39:39,668
Welcome.

527
00:39:40,586 --> 00:39:43,297
- For two, please.
- You may sit anywhere that isn't taken.

528
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:44,382
Okay.

529
00:39:44,465 --> 00:39:46,759
HEAVEN AND EARTH PC

530
00:39:47,593 --> 00:39:48,636
UNDER CONSTRUCTION

531
00:40:04,777 --> 00:40:07,029
- Excuse me, the power is out!
- What the heck?

532
00:40:07,113 --> 00:40:08,948
- What's going on?
- I was so close to winning.

533
00:40:09,031 --> 00:40:10,157
Mister.

534
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:11,409
Just testing things.

535
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:15,371
- What are you doing? Turn it back on!
- Turn the power back on!

536
00:40:15,454 --> 00:40:17,790
- We're terribly sorry!
- He's so high maintenance.

537
00:40:19,959 --> 00:40:22,169
ATTORNEY YANG DO-KYUNG

538
00:40:23,587 --> 00:40:24,755
What's up?

539
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:26,799
I have good news for you.

540
00:40:27,383 --> 00:40:29,593
The parents are willing to settle.

541
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:34,473
I told them they should never settle
with a piece of trash who beats kids.

542
00:40:35,057 --> 00:40:38,561
But an attorney has no power, you know.
I follow what my clients say.

543
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:41,772
Check the settlement agreement.
I texted it to you just now.

544
00:40:44,608 --> 00:40:45,609
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

545
00:40:47,027 --> 00:40:48,696
TOTAL AMOUNT: 150,000,000 WON

546
00:40:51,073 --> 00:40:53,784
Do you actually believe
50 million per person makes sense?

547
00:40:53,868 --> 00:40:56,620
Then, does an attorney
beating high schoolers make sense?

548
00:40:57,997 --> 00:41:02,543
When someone intellectually and socially
accomplished fails to set an example,

549
00:41:02,626 --> 00:41:05,546
they must be held accountable.

550
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:09,258
Discuss it wisely with the assailant,

551
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:13,554
and come to Taebaek by 6:00 p.m.
if you don't want I-rang to go to jail.

552
00:41:30,279 --> 00:41:31,363
Hello?

553
00:41:31,447 --> 00:41:33,365
Hello, Ms. Attorney.

554
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:36,994
The victims' attorney just called me.

555
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:40,331
They want me to come to Taebaek's office
by 6:00 p.m. for a settlement.

556
00:41:40,998 --> 00:41:43,292
Taebaek called you too?

557
00:41:43,375 --> 00:41:44,543
Yes.

558
00:41:44,627 --> 00:41:46,462
I get what they're trying to pull.

559
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:49,590
They're demanding 150 million won
for settlement money.

560
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:51,509
They must've expected

561
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:54,261
Attorney Shin wouldn't
easily agree to the big sum

562
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:55,971
and gave you a call too.

563
00:41:58,766 --> 00:42:01,560
I understand.

564
00:42:02,394 --> 00:42:04,230
I'll be there on time.

565
00:42:04,813 --> 00:42:07,274
Could you give me a little bit of time?

566
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:09,235
How much time?

567
00:42:11,028 --> 00:42:12,363
About an hour or two.

568
00:42:13,614 --> 00:42:16,075
It'll be past 6:00 by then.

569
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:23,082
Let me think only about my son right now.

570
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:27,878
I don't want him to suffer.

571
00:42:28,462 --> 00:42:31,340
I understand how you feel, but…

572
00:42:31,423 --> 00:42:32,675
It's okay.

573
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:35,094
Thank you for your concern.

574
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:51,527
I'd like you to stay away from me.

575
00:42:52,361 --> 00:42:53,487
I know from experience

576
00:42:53,571 --> 00:42:56,490
that it's better to stay away from ghosts
in dangerous situations.

577
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:02,496
Should I be with Na-hyun, then?

578
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:05,874
Sounds good.

579
00:43:09,003 --> 00:43:10,045
I'm gonna take a leak.

580
00:43:10,129 --> 00:43:11,839
- I'm going with.
- Me too.

581
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,717
Hey, just go upstairs.

582
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,260
Jun-ho might run off.

583
00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:18,178
- Wait upstairs.
- Make it quick.

584
00:43:32,276 --> 00:43:33,652
I MADE A GROUP CHAT
THANKS, BONG-SU

585
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:35,487
One is going in.

586
00:43:35,571 --> 00:43:36,655
One's here.

587
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:43,412
It's him, right?

588
00:43:44,204 --> 00:43:46,123
Yes, but why is he alone?

589
00:43:46,957 --> 00:43:48,626
Let's stick to the plan.

590
00:44:05,559 --> 00:44:06,769
Hey, kid.

591
00:44:06,852 --> 00:44:09,521
You shouldn't take my picture, gosh.

592
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:12,524
You really can't without permission.
I have rights to my own image.

593
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:14,151
Why would I take a picture of you?

594
00:44:14,234 --> 00:44:16,487
Sure, I understand.

595
00:44:16,570 --> 00:44:19,114
It's rare to run into a celebrity
in this kind of neighborhood.

596
00:44:19,198 --> 00:44:21,241
- Still--
- I'm lost for words.

597
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:23,869
Mister, I don't know who you are.

598
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:25,829
Wait. You're him, right?

599
00:44:26,455 --> 00:44:27,998
Yoon Bong-su.

600
00:44:28,082 --> 00:44:29,958
He's really famous. Don't you know him?

601
00:44:30,042 --> 00:44:31,043
This guy?

602
00:44:31,126 --> 00:44:33,921
Was it Showboating Squid?

603
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:36,590
No, Steamboating Squid! Right?
I enjoyed watching that drama!

604
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:39,760
- Oh, goodness. You watched it?
- I really liked it.

605
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:41,720
Han Na-hyun, are you really an attorney?

606
00:44:41,804 --> 00:44:42,930
You're a real celeb?

607
00:44:43,722 --> 00:44:45,140
I'd be one too, then.

608
00:44:45,224 --> 00:44:47,476
Anyway, I didn't take a picture of you.

609
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:51,188
Oh, my. My fans are so shy.

610
00:44:51,271 --> 00:44:54,441
It's okay!
You know what? You're lucky today.

611
00:44:54,525 --> 00:44:56,860
- I'll take a selfie with you. Don't worry.
- No, thanks.

612
00:44:56,944 --> 00:44:58,904
- I'll make you look good.
- Let me do it for you.

613
00:44:58,987 --> 00:44:59,988
Oh, thank you.

614
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:07,371
What the… You still have that phone?

615
00:45:07,996 --> 00:45:09,957
The attorney told us
to throw away our phones.

616
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:12,251
Did you guys do it?

617
00:45:12,835 --> 00:45:13,877
Of course.

618
00:45:14,461 --> 00:45:17,756
I got a new one with Seo-won right away.

619
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:18,841
Score!

620
00:45:21,218 --> 00:45:22,344
It's too good to waste.

621
00:45:23,178 --> 00:45:25,180
I'll toss it after showing his mom.

622
00:45:26,098 --> 00:45:27,975
She deserves to see her son's video.

623
00:45:28,725 --> 00:45:29,726
Don't you think?

624
00:45:31,019 --> 00:45:33,522
You always have a point.

625
00:45:33,605 --> 00:45:36,191
- I wish we edited a little better.
- Let me see.

626
00:45:37,234 --> 00:45:39,027
A masterpiece is a masterpiece after all.

627
00:46:02,926 --> 00:46:05,429
- The video isn't here.
- That can't be.

628
00:46:05,512 --> 00:46:08,182
- Oh, no.
- What are you doing? Give it back.

629
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:10,350
- She's looking for a camera app.
- Give it back to me.

630
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:12,019
DID YOU FIND IT?

631
00:46:18,150 --> 00:46:19,693
- Hold on…
- It's my phone.

632
00:46:21,195 --> 00:46:22,654
Damn it.

633
00:46:23,947 --> 00:46:25,324
Min-jae, run!

634
00:46:26,867 --> 00:46:28,785
- You're that guy…
- What?

635
00:46:28,869 --> 00:46:30,412
Fuck! Guys, run!

636
00:46:32,456 --> 00:46:33,665
Ow.

637
00:46:33,749 --> 00:46:34,958
Hey, stop right there!

638
00:46:35,042 --> 00:46:36,210
I got it!

639
00:46:52,309 --> 00:46:53,644
Over there!

640
00:47:02,736 --> 00:47:03,737
Attorney Yang.

641
00:47:04,738 --> 00:47:06,573
I'll send the police there.

642
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:08,742
Don't worry, and get out of there.

643
00:47:09,535 --> 00:47:11,787
You got a new phone,
so you should be okay.

644
00:47:15,582 --> 00:47:18,001
Send the police to Heaven and Earth PC
at Dream Mall quickly.

645
00:47:18,085 --> 00:47:19,169
Yes, sir.

646
00:47:39,231 --> 00:47:40,482
Did you find the video?

647
00:47:40,566 --> 00:47:43,235
No, both of them got new phones.

648
00:47:44,069 --> 00:47:46,697
- Did you catch the one who ran?
- Not yet.

649
00:47:47,281 --> 00:47:50,200
Taebaek actually demanded 150 million won
for the settlement.

650
00:47:51,159 --> 00:47:54,913
Your mother said she'd go there
to settle on your behalf.

651
00:47:54,997 --> 00:47:56,206
What time are they meeting?

652
00:47:57,791 --> 00:47:59,126
In 30 minutes.

653
00:47:59,209 --> 00:48:02,546
I'll try my best to drag it out.
Call me when you find the video.

654
00:48:03,130 --> 00:48:05,507
Okay. Please do that for me.

655
00:48:13,473 --> 00:48:14,850
I apologize.

656
00:48:15,684 --> 00:48:17,978
My son's assault is on me.

657
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:21,106
I'm to blame for not raising him better.

658
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:25,569
This will never happen again.
Please give him a chance.

659
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:28,780
How shameless of you
after what he did to those children!

660
00:49:02,356 --> 00:49:04,358
STORED

661
00:49:10,197 --> 00:49:11,531
What the fuck?

662
00:49:14,618 --> 00:49:16,662
I had a hunch, but you actually came here.

663
00:49:17,329 --> 00:49:18,455
Why are you so surprised?

664
00:49:18,538 --> 00:49:20,874
This is where you used to beat me up.

665
00:49:20,957 --> 00:49:23,251
What? Did you rat us out?

666
00:49:23,335 --> 00:49:24,836
It wasn't me.

667
00:49:28,924 --> 00:49:31,426
You wouldn't believe me, though.

668
00:49:31,510 --> 00:49:33,887
How dare you talk back to me?
Do you have a death wish?

669
00:49:33,970 --> 00:49:35,097
Why would I die?

670
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:37,933
It's your turn to die.

671
00:49:39,935 --> 00:49:41,353
Wow.

672
00:49:41,436 --> 00:49:43,647
I see you're quite fearless
now that I'm alone.

673
00:49:43,730 --> 00:49:46,108
But you're no match for me, f*****.

674
00:49:46,191 --> 00:49:48,860
Yeah, I know you can fight.

675
00:49:48,944 --> 00:49:50,445
But I won't simply take it today.

676
00:49:50,529 --> 00:49:52,447
Then what, motherf*****?

677
00:49:54,491 --> 00:49:56,368
Delete my video right now.

678
00:50:00,455 --> 00:50:01,790
You're after this too?

679
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:05,001
Amusing.

680
00:50:08,839 --> 00:50:11,591
You wanna act tough
in front of me, fucker?

681
00:50:15,470 --> 00:50:17,180
You son of a bitch.

682
00:50:20,517 --> 00:50:22,018
I wish I could beat you up to a pulp,

683
00:50:22,894 --> 00:50:25,063
but I'll stop here
because I'm quite busy today.

684
00:50:29,025 --> 00:50:30,902
- Give me your phone.
- Get off me.

685
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:33,321
Get off!

686
00:50:33,405 --> 00:50:34,906
Get off, damn it!

687
00:50:36,658 --> 00:50:38,285
Are you out of your damn mind?

688
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:44,374
Die!

689
00:50:46,835 --> 00:50:48,211
You damn nutcase.

690
00:50:54,551 --> 00:50:55,844
Give me your phone.

691
00:50:57,971 --> 00:50:59,681
Give me your phone!

692
00:51:11,401 --> 00:51:12,402
Jun-ho!

693
00:51:23,872 --> 00:51:27,167
Get off me. Get the hell off already!

694
00:51:28,418 --> 00:51:30,378
No, you're not going anywhere.

695
00:51:31,129 --> 00:51:32,380
Give me your phone.

696
00:51:32,964 --> 00:51:34,549
Then, I'll forgive you.

697
00:51:34,633 --> 00:51:35,926
Forgive me?

698
00:51:36,009 --> 00:51:37,636
You crazy asshole.

699
00:51:37,719 --> 00:51:41,306
Who do you think you are to forgive me?

700
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:43,642
I said I'll forgive you!

701
00:51:53,026 --> 00:51:54,444
You little…

702
00:52:15,715 --> 00:52:17,342
I took it away from him.

703
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:21,638
I didn't do it like them.

704
00:52:23,390 --> 00:52:24,724
I did it my way.

705
00:52:29,771 --> 00:52:31,356
How did I do?

706
00:52:34,818 --> 00:52:35,861
Well done.

707
00:52:37,070 --> 00:52:41,199
You didn't ruin your life for them.

708
00:52:43,618 --> 00:52:44,911
I'm so glad.

709
00:52:53,879 --> 00:52:57,382
TAEBAEK

710
00:53:03,597 --> 00:53:05,015
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

711
00:53:05,807 --> 00:53:07,309
TOTAL AMOUNT: 150 MILLION WON

712
00:53:16,526 --> 00:53:17,569
Excuse me.

713
00:53:25,201 --> 00:53:27,078
What do you think you're doing?

714
00:53:27,662 --> 00:53:29,915
Sung Min-jae, Na Ji-hyeok, and Lee Seo-won

715
00:53:29,998 --> 00:53:32,417
were arrested
for aggravated assault, illegal filming

716
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:34,336
and distribution of illegal content.

717
00:53:35,337 --> 00:53:39,007
They also beat Seo Jun-ho up
on the day of the assault case.

718
00:53:39,716 --> 00:53:42,636
And Lee Seo-won confessed
that Attorney Shin I-rang

719
00:53:42,719 --> 00:53:44,095
only tried to stop them.

720
00:53:44,971 --> 00:53:46,514
What are you talking about?

721
00:53:47,307 --> 00:53:48,558
Hello?

722
00:53:48,642 --> 00:53:49,851
The police?

723
00:53:49,935 --> 00:53:51,061
- Hello?
- Min-jae.

724
00:53:51,144 --> 00:53:52,437
I'll be there immediately.

725
00:53:52,520 --> 00:53:54,314
Did you do something again?

726
00:53:57,776 --> 00:54:00,362
Your son will arrive soon.
Please wait for him downstairs.

727
00:54:00,445 --> 00:54:02,405
Thank you, Ms. Attorney.

728
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:17,462
Don't you have any words for me?

729
00:54:19,297 --> 00:54:20,632
About what?

730
00:54:20,715 --> 00:54:23,301
I heard you told them
to throw their phones away.

731
00:54:23,385 --> 00:54:24,386
Is it true?

732
00:54:26,972 --> 00:54:28,223
Why are you so surprised?

733
00:54:29,057 --> 00:54:32,268
You resort to any means possible
to win a case.

734
00:54:32,352 --> 00:54:33,687
That's your way, isn't it?

735
00:54:39,359 --> 00:54:40,360
I thought

736
00:54:41,027 --> 00:54:42,654
we were the same kind.

737
00:54:46,157 --> 00:54:47,409
You haven't changed.

738
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:50,996
Is it because of Shin I-rang?

739
00:54:54,416 --> 00:54:55,750
Is he behind your change?

740
00:54:55,834 --> 00:54:56,876
Mind your own business.

741
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:59,838
Lee Gang-pung, Kim Su-a, and Jeon Sang-ho.

742
00:55:00,797 --> 00:55:03,091
- They're all dead.
- So what?

743
00:55:03,174 --> 00:55:06,011
All his clients were families
of dead people.

744
00:55:07,012 --> 00:55:09,014
Why does he only take on such cases?

745
00:55:09,597 --> 00:55:11,933
Why does he keep getting involved
with dead people?

746
00:55:12,517 --> 00:55:15,603
Besides, he swore like Lee Gang-pung
and acted like Kim Su-a.

747
00:55:15,687 --> 00:55:18,273
How did he find out
where Jeon Sang-ho's body was buried?

748
00:55:18,356 --> 00:55:19,941
Don't you find it strange at all?

749
00:55:25,530 --> 00:55:26,865
His office

750
00:55:28,575 --> 00:55:30,577
was a shaman's house
until a few months ago.

751
00:55:32,037 --> 00:55:34,622
Shin I-rang can see ghosts.

752
00:55:35,290 --> 00:55:36,708
It's dangerous to be around him.

753
00:55:38,585 --> 00:55:39,794
Stop talking nonsense.

754
00:56:19,501 --> 00:56:20,502
THURSDAY, JUNE 7, 2012

755
00:56:20,585 --> 00:56:22,337
I wonder who's more at fault.

756
00:56:22,420 --> 00:56:24,130
The one who hit them with a brick?

757
00:56:24,214 --> 00:56:26,591
Or the ones who bullied him to death?

758
00:56:26,674 --> 00:56:28,343
He had no choice…

759
00:56:28,426 --> 00:56:29,677
If I become the best attorney,

760
00:56:29,761 --> 00:56:31,012
will I be able to understand him?

761
00:56:31,096 --> 00:56:32,097
If I become the best attorney,

762
00:56:32,180 --> 00:56:36,184
will I be able to speak
for his resentment?

763
00:56:38,561 --> 00:56:40,897
No one was there to understand

764
00:56:41,940 --> 00:56:43,274
why he had to attack them.

765
00:56:43,358 --> 00:56:47,779
Who's there to understand the victim
who had no choice but to attack them?

766
00:57:00,291 --> 00:57:04,129
His office was a shaman's house
until a few months ago.

767
00:57:04,212 --> 00:57:07,340
And my office used to be a shaman's house.

768
00:57:33,491 --> 00:57:35,118
MY DAUGHTER, NA-HYUN

769
00:57:36,161 --> 00:57:37,287
Hi, Na-hyun.

770
00:57:37,370 --> 00:57:40,039
- How have you--
- Have you been to a shaman's house before?

771
00:57:41,207 --> 00:57:42,208
What?

772
00:57:42,292 --> 00:57:45,879
Have you ever visited a shaman
after that incident?

773
00:57:46,796 --> 00:57:49,174
H-How did you…

774
00:57:49,257 --> 00:57:50,967
Was it in Seocho-dong?

775
00:57:59,058 --> 00:58:01,895
I can see and communicate
with dead people.

776
00:58:01,978 --> 00:58:03,605
This time, it was Su-a.

777
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:06,608
Last time, Lee Gang-pung's spirit told me.

778
00:58:10,320 --> 00:58:11,863
You shouldn't do this to your client!

779
00:58:11,946 --> 00:58:13,615
Are you really the Han Na-hyun I know?

780
00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:16,618
What made you become this inflexible?
You're darn annoying!

781
00:58:20,455 --> 00:58:21,539
So-hyun.

782
00:58:22,832 --> 00:58:24,042
No way.

783
00:58:29,422 --> 00:58:34,260
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

784
00:58:36,763 --> 00:58:38,014
I'm sorry, Mom.

785
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:41,309
Is Attorney Han aware
that her sister has come?

786
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:42,894
No.

787
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:45,146
I don't know what to do.

788
00:58:45,730 --> 00:58:47,357
She'll be shocked if she hears it.

789
00:58:48,066 --> 00:58:50,485
Maybe it's better to keep it from her.

790
00:58:53,613 --> 00:58:55,573
For what she did this time and all,

791
00:58:55,657 --> 00:58:57,575
let's treat her to a meal sometime.

792
00:58:58,117 --> 00:58:59,953
Ask her when she's available.

793
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:03,706
Okay.

794
00:59:23,851 --> 00:59:25,144
What are you doing here?

795
00:59:45,039 --> 00:59:46,040
Na-hyun.

796
00:59:50,962 --> 00:59:51,963
Attorney Han?

797
00:59:52,880 --> 00:59:54,799
I was meaning to call you.

798
00:59:54,882 --> 00:59:56,301
Do you have time right now?

799
00:59:57,510 --> 00:59:58,761
Why do you ask?

800
00:59:58,845 --> 01:00:00,430
I need you to go somewhere with me.

801
01:00:14,193 --> 01:00:16,154
You want us to ride that?

802
01:00:17,113 --> 01:00:18,239
You don't want to?

803
01:00:18,323 --> 01:00:20,783
Well, it's not that I don't want to.

804
01:00:22,327 --> 01:00:23,453
Good, then.

805
01:00:24,120 --> 01:00:25,163
I'll go buy tickets.

806
01:00:30,126 --> 01:00:32,211
I'm afraid of heights.

807
01:00:36,633 --> 01:00:39,260
You like that?

808
01:00:39,344 --> 01:00:41,179
I go crazy for them!

809
01:00:42,722 --> 01:00:44,182
Hold on.

810
01:00:45,850 --> 01:00:49,395
Does Attorney Han know
that you like roller coasters?

811
01:00:49,479 --> 01:00:51,981
Of course! We came here
so many times on vacation.

812
01:00:54,609 --> 01:00:55,652
Then the reason

813
01:00:56,694 --> 01:00:58,154
she took me here…

814
01:01:21,928 --> 01:01:23,096
Na-hyun.

815
01:01:29,268 --> 01:01:32,021
Let's sit in the last row again today.

816
01:01:32,105 --> 01:01:33,856
- With our hands up.
- With our hands up. Deal?

817
01:01:53,167 --> 01:01:54,168
Na-hyun.

818
01:02:51,017 --> 01:02:53,019
- Is it you, So-hyun?
- It's still I-rang.

819
01:02:53,102 --> 01:02:55,438
Let me be alone with her
without you today.

820
01:02:55,521 --> 01:02:56,397
Don't you worry.

821
01:02:56,481 --> 01:02:58,858
I feel so bad for Na-hyun.

822
01:02:58,941 --> 01:03:00,818
I shouldn't stay here.

823
01:03:00,902 --> 01:03:02,361
Is it right to pass on like this?

824
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:04,781
I don't want to break her heart anymore.

825
01:03:04,864 --> 01:03:06,824
I see. It was thoughtless of me.

826
01:03:07,950 --> 01:03:09,160
Where's So-hyun?

827
01:03:09,243 --> 01:03:10,578
They all passed on.

828
01:03:10,661 --> 01:03:13,080
- No.
- Take care.

829
01:03:13,164 --> 01:03:14,415
Don't go.

830
01:03:14,499 --> 01:03:19,295
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
